      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2020-09-10</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-09-24T16:04:18Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Nonpartisan Postmaster General Act</b></p> <p>This bill restricts the political activities of the members of the Postal Service Board of Governors, including the Postmaster General and the Deputy Postmaster General.</p> <p>Specifically, the bill (1) prohibits the Postmaster General and the Deputy Postmaster General from taking an active part in political management or political campaigns; (2) prohibits the Board of Governors, the Postmaster General, and the Deputy Postmaster General from holding any political position while in office or soliciting funds for the campaign of a candidate for elected office or for a political party; and (3) restricts nominees for Postmaster General and Deputy Postmaster General to those who have not engaged in political activities in the four years prior to their appointments.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
